constructor.details: Constructor that disables initializers to prevent implementation contract initialization

exit(uint256,address,uint256,uint256).custom:error: STBL_UnauthorizedIssuer Thrown when caller is not authorized as an issuerSTBL_AssetDisabled Thrown when the asset is not active
exit(uint256,address,uint256,uint256).custom:event: exitEvent Emitted when tokens are redeemed
exit(uint256,address,uint256,uint256).details: Only callable by the asset issuer. Burns both the fungible USST tokens and the      non-fungible YLD token, then decrements the asset deposit tracking.

params._assetID: The ID of the asset being redeemed
params._from: Address from which tokens are being redeemed
params._tokenID: The ID of the YLD token (NFT) being redeemed
params._value: The amount of USST tokens to burn during redemption

fetchRegistry().details: Returns the address of the STBL Registry contract that manages asset definitions

returns._0: The address of the registry contract

fetchUSIToken().details: Returns the address of the non-fungible yield token contract

returns._0: The address of the YLD token contract

fetchUSPToken().details: Returns the address of the fungible stablecoin token contract

returns._0: The address of the USST token contract

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(address).details: Sets up access control roles, connects to registry and token contracts, and configures trusted forwarder.      Can only be called once during deployment. This replaces the constructor for upgradeable contracts.

params._registry: Address of the STBL Registry contract

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

put(address,(uint256,string,uint256,uint.custom:error: STBL_MaxLimitReached Thrown when deposit limit for asset has been reachedSTBL_UnauthorizedIssuer Thrown when caller is not authorized as an issuerSTBL_AssetDisabled Thrown when the asset is not active
put(address,(uint256,string,uint256,uint.custom:event: putEvent Emitted when tokens are issued
put(address,(uint256,string,uint256,uint.details: Only callable by the asset issuer. Checks deposit limits before minting.      Mints fungible USST tokens representing the stable value and a non-fungible YLD token      containing the asset metadata and yield information.

params._metadata: Metadata associated with the YLD NFT, including asset ID and stable value

returns._0: nftID The ID of the minted YLD token (NFT)

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

trustedForwarder().details: Implementation of the virtual function from ERC2771Context.      Returns address(0) if meta-transactions are disabled.

updateTrustedForwarder(address).custom:event: TrustedForwarderUpdated Emitted when the forwarder is updated
updateTrustedForwarder(address).details: Only callable by addresses with DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE. Setting to address(0) disables meta-transactions.

params._newForwarder: Address of the new trusted forwarder

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

version().details: Useful for tracking upgrade versions and ensuring correct implementation is deployed

returns._0: Current version number of the implementation

constructor.notice: This constructor is marked as unsafe for upgrades but is required for proper proxy pattern implementation.         The implementation contract itself should never be initialized, only proxy contracts should be.

exit(uint256,address,uint256,uint256).notice: Redeems USST and YLD tokens for a given asset

fetchUSIToken().notice: Retrieves the YLD token contract address

fetchUSPToken().notice: Retrieves the USST token contract address

put(address,(uint256,string,uint256,uint.notice: Issues USST and YLD tokens for a given asset

trustedForwarder().notice: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder for meta-transactions

updateTrustedForwarder(address).notice: Updates the trusted forwarder address for meta-transactions
